properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 17 at 5:34PM MST until January 18 at 12:00AM MST by NWS Goodland KS
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds sustained at 30 to 40 mph with gusts up
to 60 mph.

* WHERE...Cheyenne, Rawlins, Sherman, Thomas, Wallace, Logan,
Greeley and Wichita Counties.

* WHEN...Until midnight MST /1 AM CST/ tonight.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Northwest winds will increase to 30 to 40
mph with gusts up to 60 mph for several hours this evening,
mainly between 8 pm and Midnight MST.

* IMPACTS...Dangerous travel conditions are anticipated to be the
primary impact. High profile vehicles will be most at-risk,
particularly on well-traveled routes such as Interstate 70,
Highway 385, Highway 27, Highway 34, and Highway 36.
properties.instruction:
Secure loose outdoor items. Travelers in northwest Kansas are
urged to exercise additional caution this evening.

High dust concentrations can aggravate asthma and cause respiratory
problems, especially in children, the elderly, or those with pre-
existing respiratory conditions. The Kansas Department of Health
and Environment recommends taking preventative measures such as
staying indoors or wearing protective breathing masks, if
outside.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT MST /1 AM CST/ TONIGHT
